genresAdvancedInfo.name: syro-aramaic chant
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Syro-Aramaic chant is a traditional form of religious music that originated in Syria and is still practiced by Syriac Orthodox Christians today. It is characterized by its haunting melodies, intricate harmonies, and use of ancient Syriac language. Syro-Aramaic chant is often performed in churches and monasteries, and is considered an important part of Syriac Orthodox liturgy and cultural heritage.
